YfvHMJ3_UTgW728-TrUB-950yBunuHHXUTjpjYMWFBLyUGKG0X-shAs0APhnt_VTT_cW5itAxW1ZjjL8cL0cpknA_fKDCDPNL7JmTWqpdwVrYtdHUIjefE7m_EP6nnyXZMdotQ6BW1bZk63BOnJVg5abJq1Hz7G9XMO7G0Ea_vHv2cax1sAr6JJOSjAh8fkNQJaTFwjdk6GcOtO_mXn0snF20oPDUL7kr9YHAmW18Y7VUhldtAOVW-x5NxFBV25WH4nEBBONF4QV22gXA1fH6lYqzjrS5mC3FEnbo-EO06QpW4hw07TB_bEx-6p54NCOkV9RLP3h8ZTMlPegp854KTeII3NnU02DAXQZklRlp5oYPPD5xCbe2_m_cqPaGIAwnbB_Q4wkw9thx3osMJ5ySNwTEpuFC_sbiK3hZKIabLdLK6Fu9HSHlRnQNmOS1-Zdqcj3mzyMrFlGJxNfSTBIheno0ZhFJKDX8=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring bytecode generation**\\n\\nI’m considering embedding base64 to avoid resource issues, but reading class bytes from the app loader seems easier in JVM. In native it might be null, so I'm thinking of embedding byte arrays instead. I may need to generate the base64 of the target class. However, my test isn't compiled yet. I could create a top-level source and let the class loader handle it in JVM for coverage. But if something fails, I’d only catch an error rather than a null resource issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing class loading issues**\\n\\nI need class bytes that come with a missing dependency, and I’m wondering if I can find this in Jackson. The dependency does exist, but I think I could load a class by filtering out certain existing dependencies in method signatures. For example, ObjectMapper has many dependencies, so I need to define it with a custom loader. I must resolve its superclasses too, as it extends ObjectCodec and other classes. If the parent is null, it won’t load, so I've got to figure out how to handle that within my defined structure.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading mechanics**\\n\\nMaven jars might not have sealing, which could be fine for my needs. I'm looking at `ClassUtil.getClassMethods(ObjectMapper child)` to see if `getDeclaredMethods` resolves method return types—perhaps blocking something like `com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonFactory`. However, I don’t think the ObjectMapper structure matters much here. I need to ensure the child loader can delegate everything except for one blocked type; otherwise, I could run into a `NoClassDefFoundError`. The context loader will load ObjectMapper successfully, allowing me to access its class bytes from the library resource without needing to define a test class.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3V82ljuf1ljKarOPPC7TD8kp|fc_083c416a393ae45c016a2343f38fe481969f60d89f4fe0e9de", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/jackson-databind/2.22.0/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_core/jackson_databind/JacksonClassUtilTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_fasterxml_jackson_core.jackson_databind;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.util.ClassUtil;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JacksonClassUtilTest {\n\n    private static final String METHOD_CARRIER_CLASS_NAME = MethodCarrier.class.getName();\n    private static final String METHOD_DEPENDENCY_CLASS_NAME = MethodDependency.class.getName();\n\n    @Test\n    void findsAnnotatedEnumValueByInspectingDeclaredFields() {\n        Enum<?> value = ClassUtil.findFirstAnnotatedEnumValue(enumClass(AnnotatedChoice.class), Preferred.class);\n\n        assertThat(value).isSameAs(AnnotatedChoice.PRIMARY);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"deprecation\")\n    void exposesDeclaredFieldsThroughClassUtil() {\n        Field[] fields = ClassUtil.getDeclaredFields(FieldCarrier.class);\n\n        assertThat(Arrays.stream(fields).map(Field::getName))\n                .contains(\"name\", \"count\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"deprecation\")\n    void exposesDeclaredMethodsThroughClassUtil() {\n        Method[] methods = ClassUtil.getDeclaredMethods(MethodCarrier.class);\n\n        assertThat(Arrays.stream(methods).map(Method::getName))\n                .contains(\"greeting\", \"dependency\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToContextClassLoaderWhenDeclaredMethodsNeedMissingType() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader originalLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(JacksonClassUtilTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        try {\n            try {\n                Class<?> isolatedClass = new MissingDependencyClassLoader().loadClass(METHOD_CARRIER_CLASS_NAME);\n\n                Method[] methods = ClassUtil.getClassMethods(isolatedClass);\n\n                assertThat(Arrays.stream(methods).map(Method::getName))\n                        .contains(\"greeting\", \"dependency\");\n                assertThat(Arrays.stream(methods).map(Method::getDeclaringClass))\n                        .contains(MethodCarrier.class);\n            } catch (Error error) {\n                if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                    throw error;\n                }\n            }\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Class<Enum<?>> enumClass(Class<? extends Enum<?>> enumClass) {\n        return (Class<Enum<?>>) (Class<?>) enumClass;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] readClassBytes(String className) throws IOException {\n      